This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) as it deals with the spread of information on social media. It could also belong to the sub-category of Software Engineering (cs.SE) as it proposes a new probabilistic model. Other possible sub-categories include Statistical Learning (cs.LG) as the model is probabilistic, Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) as the model deals with messages containing URLs, and Systems and Control (cs.SY) as the model aims to predict the spread of information. However, given the focus on social media and user behavior, Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) and Social Computing (cs.SOC) are more likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper could also belong to the sub-category of Sound (cs.SD) as it deals with the visibility and adoption of items, which could be related to the audibility and propagation of sound waves.
